  "sourceRequest": "Create a quantitative silver chloride precipitation lab where students compare Q with Ksp, filter and dry the product, and weigh it on a balance.",
  "metadata": {
    "title": "Silver chloride precipitation",
    "learningObjective": "Use Q and Ksp to explain silver chloride precipitation, then collect and weigh the dry product by gravimetry.",
    "studentSummary": "Combine measured silver nitrate and sodium chloride solutions, inspect the Q versus Ksp result, then filter, dry, and weigh the silver chloride.",
    "gradeBand": "11-12",
    "estimatedMinutes": 25,
    "difficulty": "intermediate",
    "tags": ["precipitation", "solubility", "net ionic", "gravimetry"],
    "accessibilityNotes": [
      "Precipitate presence and colour are reported as text, never colour alone.",
      "Procedure basis: Royal Society of Chemistry, Gravimetric analysis practical videos for 16-18 students (filter, wash, dry, and measure silver chloride)."
    ],
